\"Choose edition Search singapore asia world opinion life business sport Visual Podcasts SPH Rewards\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 98}, {\"ngram\": \"Paid press releases\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 132}, {\"ngram\": \"Advertise\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest sports news\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 206}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 220}, {\"ngram\": \"07:55 AM\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 266}, {\"ngram\": \"UpdatedAug\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 277}, {\"ngram\": \"05:26 AM PARIS\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 302}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead-up\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 317}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"many doubts\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"the French capital\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest sporting spectacle\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were concerns over heatwaves and security risksamid political uncertainty in France,and Parisians displayed little enthusiasm as the clock ticked down to the Games.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999994471478822, \"rank\": 4.873138479701897e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"heatwaves\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"risksamid political uncertainty\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 571}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"little enthusiasm\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 661}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris came to life over the past fortnight as it welcomed more than 10,700 athletes from 200 countries and territories, who battled it out across 32 sports.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.857245225977983e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"the past fortnight\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 10,700 athletes\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"200 countries\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"territories\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"32 sports\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a stark contrast to the Tokyo Games in 2021, which were held in empty stadiums due to the Covid-19 pandemic, the last 17 days have delivered world-class sporting action in front of packed stands at iconic venues such as the Grand Palais.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stark contrast\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"empty stadiums\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-19 pandemic\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"the last 17 days\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"world-class sporting action\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"packed stands\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"iconic venues\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Palais\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States topped the medal table for the fourth straight Games, although it came down to the very last event on Aug 11 for the Americans to do so.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999964527964197, \"rank\": 3.534459330274416e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medal table\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"the fourth straight Games\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"the very last event\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1184}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going into the final day, the US had 38 golds, while China led with 39.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5321809227069662, \"rank\": 0.5963595326802014, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999996775841, \"rank\": 1.6951537087311545e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final day\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"38 golds\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Chinese weightlifter Li Wenwen clinched one gold in the women's 81kg event, the Americans claimed two, first through cyclist Jennifer Valente and then via the women's basketball team, who claimed their eighth consecutive Olympic title.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7979559