title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Unlikethe ambitious effort\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"a more conventional and mellow ceremony\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2262}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Golden Voyager performs during the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A Golden Voyager\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS Ahead of the closing ceremony, executive director Thierry Reboul admitted that he had to review the script \\\"for the umpteenth time\\\" after a scene from the opening ceremony, which was interpreted as parodying The Last Supper, drew backlash from Christian groups worldwide.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6016621045432668e-19, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}, {\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8311182844883914, \"rank\": 0.12826161916646317, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2336}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2375}, {\"ngram\": \"the script\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"the umpteenth time\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2476}, {\"ngram\": \"a scene\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"backlash\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sketch featured drag queens, a transgender model, a naked singer dressed up as the Greek god of wine Dionysus, and while Reboul maintained that it was in reference to a 17th-century Dutch painting of the Greek Olympian gods, he and artistic director Thomas Jolly received death threats.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2707, \"end\": 2712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9969751859018817, \"rank\": 0.0020585727131729363, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.457472312585863e-24, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2806, \"end\": 2811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999182392468532, \"rank\": 6.727932152197123e-05, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9969751859018817, \"rank\": 0.0020585727131729363, \"text\": \"Gr